cpp.Finalizable.name: Finalizable
cpp.Finalizable.description:
This is just a helper class. It is not actually required to inherit from this
to use NativeGc.addFinalizable(this,inPin), only a function called
finalize is needed.

cpp.Lib.name: Lib
cpp.Lib.description:
Platform-specific Cpp Library. Provides some platform-specific functions
for the C++ target, such as conversion from Haxe types to native types
and vice-versa.

cpp.ConstStar.name: ConstStar
cpp.ConstStar.description:
Allows haxe to type the result correctly, and hxcpp can recognise this uses
the correct type.

cpp.Reference.name: Reference
cpp.Reference.description:
Allows haxe to type result correctly, and hxcpp can recognise this and
prevent unwanted casting.

cpp.Star.name: Star
cpp.Star.description:
Allows haxe to type result correctly, and hxcpp can recognise this use the
correct type.

cpp.Struct.name: Struct
cpp.Struct.description: Wraps external types with a class that integrates with Dynamic.

cpp.VarArg.name: VarArg
cpp.VarArg.description:
Allows haxe to type params correctly, and hxcpp can recognise this use the
correct type.

cs.Lib.name: Lib
cs.Lib.description:
Platform-specific C# Library. Provides some platform-specific functions for the C# target,
such as conversion from haxe types to native types and vice-versa.

cs.Syntax.name: Syntax
cs.Syntax.description:
Generate C# syntax not directly supported by Haxe.
Use only at low-level when specific target-specific code-generation is required.

cs.CsClass.name: CsClass
cs.CsClass.description:
The type argument must be a reference type. This constraint applies also to
any class, interface, delegate, or array type.

cs.Flags.name: Flags
cs.Flags.description: Use this type to have access to the bitwise operators of C# enums that have a cs.system.FlagsAttribute attribute.

cs.Pointer.name: Pointer
cs.Pointer.description:
This type represents pointer types for C# function parameters. It should only
be used inside an unsafe context (not checked by the Haxe compiler)

cs.Out.name: Out
cs.Out.description:
This type represents "out" types for C# function parameters.
It only has effect on function parameters, and conversion to/from the referenced type is automatic.

cs.Ref.name: Ref
cs.Ref.description:
This type represents "ref" types for C# function parameters.
It only has effect on function parameters, and conversion to/from the referenced type is automatic.

flash.Lib.name: Lib
flash.Lib.description:
Platform-specific Flash Library. Provides some platform-specific
functions for the Flash target.

flash.Vector.name: Vector
flash.Vector.description: The Vector class is very similar to Array but is only supported by the Flash Player 10+

flash.AnyType.name: AnyType
flash.AnyType.description:
This type represents the Flash * type, which is
actually the absense of type. It can be used as a
type parameter for flash.Vector to represent the
native Vector.<*> type.

haxe.EntryPoint.name: EntryPoint
haxe.EntryPoint.description:
If haxe.MainLoop is kept from DCE, then we will insert an haxe.EntryPoint.run() call just at then end of main().
This class can be redefined by custom frameworks so they can handle their own main loop logic.

haxe.EnumTools.name: EnumTools
haxe.EnumTools.description:
This class provides advanced methods on enums. It is ideally used with
using EnumTools and then acts as an
extension to the
enum types.

haxe.EnumValueTools.name: EnumValueTools
haxe.EnumValueTools.description:
This class provides advanced methods on enum values. It is ideally used with
using EnumValueTools and then acts as an
extension to the
EnumValue types.

haxe.Int64Helper.name: Int64Helper
haxe.Int64Helper.description: Helper for parsing to Int64 instances.

haxe.Json.name: Json
haxe.Json.description:
Cross-platform JSON API: it will automatically use the optimized native API if available.
Use -D haxeJSON to force usage of the Haxe implementation even if a native API is found:
This will provide extra encoding features such as enums (replaced by their index) and StringMaps.

haxe.Log.name: Log
haxe.Log.description:
Log primarily provides the trace() method, which is invoked upon a call to
trace() in Haxe code.

haxe.Resource.name: Resource
haxe.Resource.description:
Resource can be used to access resources that were added through the
--resource file@name command line parameter.

haxe.Serializer.name: Serializer
haxe.Serializer.description:
The Serializer class can be used to encode values and objects into a String,
from which the Unserializer class can recreate the original representation.

haxe.Template.name: Template
haxe.Template.description:
Template provides a basic templating mechanism to replace values in a source
String, and to have some basic logic.

haxe.Timer.name: Timer
haxe.Timer.description:
The Timer class allows you to create asynchronous timers on platforms that
support events.

haxe.Unserializer.name: Unserializer
haxe.Unserializer.description:
The Unserializer class is the complement to the Serializer class. It parses
a serialization String and creates objects from the contained data.

haxe.Utf8.name: Utf8
haxe.Utf8.description:
Since not all platforms guarantee that String always uses UTF-8 encoding, you
can use this cross-platform API to perform operations on such strings.

haxe.CallStack.name: CallStack
haxe.CallStack.description: Get information about the call stack.

haxe.Constructible.name: Constructible
haxe.Constructible.description:
This type unifies with any instance of classes that have a constructor
which

haxe.DynamicAccess.name: DynamicAccess
haxe.DynamicAccess.description:
DynamicAccess is an abstract type for working with anonymous structures
that are intended to hold collections of objects by the string key.

haxe.EnumFlags.name: EnumFlags
haxe.EnumFlags.description:
A typed interface for bit flags. This is not a real object, only a typed
interface for an actual Int. Each flag can be tested/set with the
corresponding enum instance. Up to 32 flags can be stored that way.

haxe.FlatEnum.name: FlatEnum
haxe.FlatEnum.description:
This type unifies with an enum instance if all constructors of the enum
require no arguments.

haxe.Function.name: Function
haxe.Function.description: This type unifies with any function type.

haxe.Int32.name: Int32
haxe.Int32.description:
Int32 provides a 32-bit integer with consistent overflow behavior across
all platforms.

haxe.Int64.name: Int64
haxe.Int64.description:
A cross-platform signed 64-bit integer.
Int64 instances can be created from two 32-bit words using Int64.make().

haxe.NotVoid.name: NotVoid
haxe.NotVoid.description: This type unifies with anything but Void.

haxe.Rest.name: Rest
haxe.Rest.description: A special type that represents a "rest" function argument.

haxe.PosInfos.name: PosInfos
haxe.PosInfos.description:
PosInfos is a magic type which can be used to generate position information
into the output for debugging use.

hl.Format.name: Format
hl.Format.description: These are the bindings for the HL fmt.hdll library, which contains various low level formats handling.

hl.UI.name: UI
hl.UI.description: These are the bindings for the HL ui.hdll library, which contains some low level system access.

java.Lib.name: Lib
java.Lib.description:
Platform-specific Java Library. Provides some platform-specific functions for the Java target,
such as conversion from Haxe types to native types and vice-versa.

js.Lib.name: Lib
js.Lib.description:
Platform-specific JavaScript Library. Provides some platform-specific functions
for the JavaScript target.

js.Syntax.name: Syntax
js.Syntax.description:
Generate JavaScript syntax not directly supported by Haxe.
Use only at low-level when specific target-specific code-generation is required.

lua.Bit.name: Bit
lua.Bit.description: Externs for the "bit" class that is required for Haxe lua

lua.HaxeIterator.name: HaxeIterator
lua.HaxeIterator.description:
An implementation of the Haxe iterator data structure needed for identical
lua iterator behavior.

lua.Lib.name: Lib
lua.Lib.description:
Platform-specific Lua Library. Provides some platform-specific functions
for the Lua target, such as conversion from Haxe types to native types
and vice-versa.

lua.Lua.name: Lua
lua.Lua.description: These are all global static methods within Lua.

lua.NativeStringTools.name: NativeStringTools
lua.NativeStringTools.description:
These are all externs for the base Lua "string" class, which functions
as an additional set of string tools.

lua.PairTools.name: PairTools
lua.PairTools.description: A set of utility methods for working with the Lua table extern.

lua.Table.name: Table
lua.Table.description: This library provides generic functions for table manipulation.

lua.TableTools.name: TableTools
lua.TableTools.description:
This library is an extern for a polyfill library of common lua table
methods.

lua.Thread.name: Thread
lua.Thread.description:
The sole purpose of this extern is to provide a concrete type for
basic reflection purposes.

lua.CollectGarbageOption.name: CollectGarbageOption
lua.CollectGarbageOption.description: Enum for describing garbage collection options

lua.CoroutineState.name: CoroutineState
lua.CoroutineState.description: A enumerator that describes the output of Coroutine.status().

lua.IoType.name: IoType
lua.IoType.description: A enumerator that describes the output of Io.type().

lua.NativeIterator.name: NativeIterator
lua.NativeIterator.description:
This abstract enables easy conversion from basic lua iterators
(i.e., a function that is called until it returns null), and
Haxe iterators, which provide a next/hasNext interface.

lua.DateType.name: DateType
lua.DateType.description: A typedef that describes the output of Os.date().

lua.DebugInfo.name: DebugInfo
lua.DebugInfo.description: A enumerator that describes the output of Debug.getinfo().

lua.TimeParam.name: TimeParam
lua.TimeParam.description: A typedef that matches the date parameter Os.time() will accept.

neko.Lib.name: Lib
neko.Lib.description:
Platform-specific Neko Library. Provides some platform-specific functions
for the Neko target, such as conversion from Haxe types to native types
and vice-versa.

neko.Web.name: Web
neko.Web.description:
This class is used for accessing the local Web server and the current
client request and information.

php.BadFunctionCallException.name: BadFunctionCallException
php.BadFunctionCallException.description:
Exception thrown if a callback refers to an undefined function
or if some arguments are missing.

php.BadMethodCallException.name: BadMethodCallException
php.BadMethodCallException.description:
Exception thrown if a callback refers to an undefined method
or if some arguments are missing.

php.Const.name: Const
php.Const.description:
This class contains externs for native PHP constants defined in global namespace.
For native PHP functions in global namespace see php.Global.

php.DomainException.name: DomainException
php.DomainException.description: Exception thrown if a value does not adhere to a defined valid data domain.

php.Generator.name: Generator
php.Generator.description:
Generator is not a Haxe Iterable. It can be iterated one time only.
Unfortunately Haxe does not know that in PHP generators may have no return expression or return value with any type of value.
Use return null or untyped cast to workaround this issue:

php.Global.name: Global
php.Global.description:
This class contains externs for native PHP functions defined in global namespace.
For native PHP constants in global namespace see php.Const.

php.InvalidArgumentException.name: InvalidArgumentException
php.InvalidArgumentException.description: Exception thrown if an argument is not of the expected type.

php.LengthException.name: LengthException
php.LengthException.description: Exception thrown if a length is invalid.

php.Lib.name: Lib
php.Lib.description:
Platform-specific PHP Library. Provides some platform-specific functions
for the PHP target, such as conversion from Haxe types to native types
and vice-versa.

php.LogicException.name: LogicException
php.LogicException.description:
Exception that represents error in the program logic.
This kind of exception should lead directly to a fix in your code.

php.OutOfBoundsException.name: OutOfBoundsException
php.OutOfBoundsException.description:
Exception thrown if a value is not a valid key.
This represents errors that cannot be detected at compile time.

php.OutOfRangeException.name: OutOfRangeException
php.OutOfRangeException.description:
Exception thrown when an illegal index was requested.
This represents errors that should be detected at compile time.

php.OverflowException.name: OverflowException
php.OverflowException.description: Exception thrown when adding an element to a full container.

php.RangeException.name: RangeException
php.RangeException.description:
Exception thrown to indicate range errors during program execution.
Normally this means there was an arithmetic error other than under/overflow.

php.RuntimeException.name: RuntimeException
php.RuntimeException.description: Exception thrown if an error which can only be found on runtime occurs.

php.Session.name: Session
php.Session.description:
Session consists of a way to preserve certain data across
subsequent accesses.

php.Syntax.name: Syntax
php.Syntax.description:
Special extern class to support PHP language specifics.
Don't use these functions unless you are really sure what you are doing.

php.UnderflowException.name: UnderflowException
php.UnderflowException.description:
Exception thrown when performing an invalid operation on an empty container,
such as removing an element.

php.UnexpectedValueException.name: UnexpectedValueException
php.UnexpectedValueException.description:
Exception thrown if a value does not match with a set of values.
Typically this happens when a function calls another function and
expects the return value to be of a certain type or value not including
arithmetic or buffer related errors.

php.Web.name: Web
php.Web.description:
This class is used for accessing the local Web server and the current
client request and information.

php.NativeStructArray.name: NativeStructArray
php.NativeStructArray.description:
This type can be used in places where externs use associative arrays as a list of configuration options.
This type is a special case for Haxe->Php generator: object declaration is generated as php array declaration whenever
that object declaration is passed directly to a variable or a function argument of this type.

php.Ref.name: Ref
php.Ref.description:
Special type which allows passing function arguments by reference.
This type should be used for externs only.

php.Scalar.name: Scalar
php.Scalar.description: Scalar is a type that is compatible with any scalar value (int, float, bool, string)

python.Lib.name: Lib
python.Lib.description:
Platform-specific Python Library. Provides some platform-specific functions
for the Python target, such as conversion from Haxe types to native types
and vice-versa.

python.KwArgs.name: KwArgs
python.KwArgs.description:
This type represents python **kwargs feature, supporting
passing named arguments to a function.

python.NativeIterable.name: NativeIterable
python.NativeIterable.description:
This type represents native Python iterables (objects that implement __iter__() method).
It supports Haxe iteration and conversion to Iterable by creating wrapper objects.

python.NativeIterator.name: NativeIterator
python.NativeIterator.description:
This type represents native Python iterators.
It supports automatic conversion to Haxe Iterator by creating wrapper object.

python.VarArgs.name: VarArgs
python.VarArgs.description:
This type represents python *args feature, supporting
passing arbitrary number of arguments to a function.

sys.FileSystem.name: FileSystem
sys.FileSystem.description: This class provides information about files and directories.

sys.FileStat.name: FileStat
sys.FileStat.description: File information, as given by sys.FileSystem.stat.

cpp.net.ThreadServer.name: ThreadServer
cpp.net.ThreadServer.description:
The ThreadServer can be used to easily create a multithreaded server where each thread polls multiple connections.
To use it, at a minimum you must override or rebind clientConnected, readClientMessage, and clientMessage and you must define your Client and Message.

cpp.rtti.FieldIntegerLookup.name: FieldIntegerLookup
cpp.rtti.FieldIntegerLookup.description:
If you implement this interface, then the backend will generate code that
allows fast dynamic access to fields by integer id.  This should speed up the CFFI.

cpp.rtti.FieldNumericIntegerLookup.name: FieldNumericIntegerLookup
cpp.rtti.FieldNumericIntegerLookup.description:
If you implement this interface, then the backend will generate code that
allows fast numeric access to fields by integer id.  This should speed up the CFFI.

cpp.vm.Debugger.name: Debugger
cpp.vm.Debugger.description:
This class wraps the hxcpp C++ implementation to provide a Haxe interface
to the low level debugging features

cpp.vm.Parameter.name: Parameter
cpp.vm.Parameter.description:
Parameter describes a function parameter. Instances of this class are
embedded in stack frame objects to describe the function parameters that
were used in the invocation of the function that defines that stack frame.

cpp.vm.StackFrame.name: StackFrame
cpp.vm.StackFrame.description: StackFrame describes one call stack frame.

cpp.vm.ThreadInfo.name: ThreadInfo
cpp.vm.ThreadInfo.description: ThreadInfo describes the state of a single thread.

eval.luv.LuvException.name: LuvException
eval.luv.LuvException.description: Exceptions thrown by functions in eval.luv package.

eval.luv.Version.name: Version
eval.luv.Version.description: Version information for the vendored libuv.

eval.luv.FileModeNumeric.name: FileModeNumeric
eval.luv.FileModeNumeric.description:
Abstract type for a bit field of permissions bits, i.e., an int in which
multiple bits may be set. These bit fields are returned by operations such
as eval.luv.File.stat

eval.luv.Redirection.name: Redirection
eval.luv.Redirection.description: File descriptor redirections for use with eval.luv.Process.spawn

eval.luv.SigNum.name: SigNum
eval.luv.SigNum.description:
For the moment, the signals exposed are those that are both present on Unix
and present or emulated by libuv on Windows.

eval.vm.Gc.name: Gc
eval.vm.Gc.description: Memory management control and statistics; finalised values.

eval.vm.Control.name: Control
eval.vm.Control.description: The GC parameters are given as a control record. Note that these parameters can also be initialised by setting the OCAMLRUNPARAM environment variable. See the documentation of ocamlrun.

eval.vm.Stat.name: Stat
eval.vm.Stat.description:
The memory management counters are returned in a stat record.
The total amount of memory allocated by the program since it was started is (in words) minor_words + major_words - promoted_words. Multiply by the word size (4 on a 32-bit machine, 8 on a 64-bit machine) to get the number of bytes.

haxe.crypto.Adler32.name: Adler32
haxe.crypto.Adler32.description: Calculates the Adler32 of the given Bytes.

haxe.crypto.Base64.name: Base64
haxe.crypto.Base64.description: Allows one to encode/decode String and bytes using Base64 encoding.

haxe.crypto.BaseCode.name: BaseCode
haxe.crypto.BaseCode.description: Allows one to encode/decode String and bytes using a power of two base dictionary.

haxe.crypto.Crc32.name: Crc32
haxe.crypto.Crc32.description: Calculates the Crc32 of the given Bytes.

haxe.crypto.Hmac.name: Hmac
haxe.crypto.Hmac.description: Calculates a Hmac of the given Bytes using a HashMethod.

haxe.crypto.Md5.name: Md5
haxe.crypto.Md5.description: Creates a MD5 of a String.

haxe.crypto.Sha1.name: Sha1
haxe.crypto.Sha1.description: Creates a Sha1 of a String.

haxe.crypto.Sha224.name: Sha224
haxe.crypto.Sha224.description: Creates a Sha224 of a String.

haxe.crypto.Sha256.name: Sha256
haxe.crypto.Sha256.description: Creates a Sha256 of a String.

haxe.display.DisplayMethods.name: DisplayMethods
haxe.display.DisplayMethods.description:
Methods of the JSON-RPC-based --display protocol in Haxe 4.
A lot of the methods are inspired by the Language Server Protocol, but there is no intention to be directly compatible with it.

haxe.display.Location.name: Location
haxe.display.Location.description: Represents a location inside a resource, such as a line inside a text file.

haxe.display.Position.name: Position
haxe.display.Position.description: Position in a text document expressed as 1-based line and character offset.

haxe.display.Range.name: Range
haxe.display.Range.description: A range in a text document expressed as (1-based) start and end positions.

haxe.display.Version.name: Version
haxe.display.Version.description: Represents a semantic version, see https://semver.org/.

haxe.ds.ArraySort.name: ArraySort
haxe.ds.ArraySort.description:
ArraySort provides a stable implementation of merge sort through its sort
method. It should be used instead of Array.sort in cases where the order
of equal elements has to be retained on all targets.

haxe.ds.BalancedTree.name: BalancedTree
haxe.ds.BalancedTree.description:
BalancedTree allows key-value mapping with arbitrary keys, as long as they
can be ordered. By default, Reflect.compare is used in the compare
method, which can be overridden in subclasses.

haxe.ds.EnumValueMap.name: EnumValueMap
haxe.ds.EnumValueMap.description: EnumValueMap allows mapping of enum value keys to arbitrary values.

haxe.ds.IntMap.name: IntMap
haxe.ds.IntMap.description: IntMap allows mapping of Int keys to arbitrary values.

haxe.ds.List.name: List
haxe.ds.List.description:
A linked-list of elements. The list is composed of element container objects
that are chained together. It is optimized so that adding or removing an
element does not imply copying the whole list content every time.

haxe.ds.ListSort.name: ListSort
haxe.ds.ListSort.description:
ListSort provides a stable implementation of merge sort through its sort
method. It has a O(N.log(N)) complexity and does not require additional memory allocation.

haxe.ds.ObjectMap.name: ObjectMap
haxe.ds.ObjectMap.description: ObjectMap allows mapping of object keys to arbitrary values.

haxe.ds.StringMap.name: StringMap
haxe.ds.StringMap.description: StringMap allows mapping of String keys to arbitrary values.

haxe.ds.UnsafeStringMap.name: UnsafeStringMap
haxe.ds.UnsafeStringMap.description:
This is similar to StringMap excepts that it does not sanitize the keys.
As a result, it will be faster to access the map for reading, but it might fail
with some reserved keys such as constructor or prototype.

haxe.ds.WeakMap.name: WeakMap
haxe.ds.WeakMap.description: WeakMap allows mapping of object keys to arbitrary values.

haxe.ds.HashMap.name: HashMap
haxe.ds.HashMap.description: HashMap allows mapping of hashable objects to arbitrary values.

haxe.ds.Map.name: Map
haxe.ds.Map.description:
Map allows key to value mapping for arbitrary value types, and many key
types.

haxe.ds.ReadOnlyArray.name: ReadOnlyArray
haxe.ds.ReadOnlyArray.description:
ReadOnlyArray is an abstract over an ordinary Array which only exposes
APIs that don't modify the instance, hence "read-only".

haxe.ds.Vector.name: Vector
haxe.ds.Vector.description:
A Vector is a storage of fixed size. It can be faster than Array on some
targets, and is never slower.

haxe.ds.Either.name: Either
haxe.ds.Either.description:
Either represents values which are either of type L (Left) or type R
(Right).

haxe.ds.Option.name: Option
haxe.ds.Option.description:
An Option is a wrapper type which can either have a value (Some) or not a
value (None).

haxe.exceptions.ArgumentException.name: ArgumentException
haxe.exceptions.ArgumentException.description: An exception that is thrown when an invalid value provided for an argument of a function.

haxe.exceptions.NotImplementedException.name: NotImplementedException
haxe.exceptions.NotImplementedException.description: An exception that is thrown when requested function or operation does not have an implementation.

haxe.exceptions.PosException.name: PosException
haxe.exceptions.PosException.description: An exception that carry position information of a place where it was created.

haxe.extern.AsVar.name: AsVar
haxe.extern.AsVar.description:
If this type is used as an argument type, the compiler ensures that
argument expressions are bound to a local variable.

haxe.extern.EitherType.name: EitherType
haxe.extern.EitherType.description:
An abstract type allowing values to be either of T1 or T2 type.
Supports implicit casts from/to either types.

haxe.format.JsonParser.name: JsonParser
haxe.format.JsonParser.description: An implementation of JSON parser in Haxe.

haxe.format.JsonPrinter.name: JsonPrinter
haxe.format.JsonPrinter.description: An implementation of JSON printer in Haxe.

haxe.http.HttpBase.name: HttpBase
haxe.http.HttpBase.description:
This class can be used to handle Http requests consistently across
platforms. There are two intended usages:

haxe.http.HttpMethod.name: HttpMethod
haxe.http.HttpMethod.description:
HTTP defines methods (sometimes referred to as verbs) to indicate the desired action to be
performed on the identified resource. What this resource represents, whether pre-existing data
or data that is generated dynamically, depends on the implementation of the server.

haxe.io.Eof.name: Eof
haxe.io.Eof.description: This exception is raised when reading while data is no longer available in the haxe.io.Input.

haxe.io.FPHelper.name: FPHelper
haxe.io.FPHelper.description:
Helper that converts between floating point and binary representation.
Always works in low-endian encoding.

haxe.io.Input.name: Input
haxe.io.Input.description:
An Input is an abstract reader. See other classes in the haxe.io package
for several possible implementations.

haxe.io.Output.name: Output
haxe.io.Output.description:
An Output is an abstract write. A specific output implementation will only
have to override the writeByte and maybe the write, flush and close
methods. See File.write and String.write for two ways of creating an
Output.

haxe.io.Path.name: Path
haxe.io.Path.description:
This class provides a convenient way of working with paths. It supports the
common path formats:

haxe.io.Scheme.name: Scheme
haxe.io.Scheme.description:
A scheme consists of a sequence of characters beginning with a letter and followed
by any combination of letters, digits, plus (+, period (.), or hyphen (-).

haxe.io.Encoding.name: Encoding
haxe.io.Encoding.description: String binary encoding supported by Haxe I/O

haxe.io.Error.name: Error
haxe.io.Error.description: The possible IO errors that can occur

haxe.iterators.ArrayIterator.name: ArrayIterator
haxe.iterators.ArrayIterator.description: This iterator is used only when Array<T> is passed to Iterable<T>

haxe.iterators.DynamicAccessIterator.name: DynamicAccessIterator
haxe.iterators.DynamicAccessIterator.description: This iterator can be used to iterate over the values of haxe.DynamicAccess.

haxe.iterators.DynamicAccessKeyValueIter.name: DynamicAccessKeyValueIterator
haxe.iterators.DynamicAccessKeyValueIter.description: This Key/Value iterator can be used to iterate over haxe.DynamicAccess.

haxe.iterators.MapKeyValueIterator.name: MapKeyValueIterator
haxe.iterators.MapKeyValueIterator.description: This Key/Value iterator can be used to iterate across maps.

haxe.iterators.StringIterator.name: StringIterator
haxe.iterators.StringIterator.description: This iterator can be used to iterate over char codes in a string.

haxe.iterators.StringIteratorUnicode.name: StringIteratorUnicode
haxe.iterators.StringIteratorUnicode.description:
This iterator can be used to iterate across strings in a cross-platform
way. It handles surrogate pairs on platforms that require it. On each
iteration, it returns the next character code.

haxe.iterators.StringKeyValueIterator.name: StringKeyValueIterator
haxe.iterators.StringKeyValueIterator.description: This iterator can be used to iterate over char indexes and char codes in a string.

haxe.iterators.StringKeyValueIteratorUni.name: StringKeyValueIteratorUnicode
haxe.iterators.StringKeyValueIteratorUni.description:
This iterator can be used to iterate across strings in a cross-platform
way. It handles surrogate pairs on platforms that require it. On each
iteration, it returns the next character offset as key and the next
character code as value.

haxe.macro.CompilationServer.name: CompilationServer
haxe.macro.CompilationServer.description:
This class provides some methods which can be invoked from command line using
--macro server.field(args).

haxe.macro.Compiler.name: Compiler
haxe.macro.Compiler.description: All these methods can be called for compiler configuration macros.

haxe.macro.ComplexTypeTools.name: ComplexTypeTools
haxe.macro.ComplexTypeTools.description:
This class provides some utility methods to work with AST-level types. It is
best used through using haxe.macro.ComplexTypeTools syntax and then provides
additional methods on haxe.macro.ComplexType instances.

haxe.macro.Context.name: Context
haxe.macro.Context.description: Context provides an API for macro programming.

haxe.macro.Error.name: Error
haxe.macro.Error.description: This error can be used to handle or produce compilation errors in macros.

haxe.macro.ExprArrayTools.name: ExprArrayTools
haxe.macro.ExprArrayTools.description:
This class provides functions on expression arrays for convenience. For a
detailed reference on each method, see the documentation of ExprTools.

haxe.macro.ExprTools.name: ExprTools
haxe.macro.ExprTools.description:
This class provides some utility methods to work with expressions. It is
best used through 'using haxe.macro.ExprTools' syntax and then provides
additional methods on haxe.macro.Expr instances.

haxe.macro.Format.name: Format
haxe.macro.Format.description: The actual macro implemented for Std.format

haxe.macro.MacroStringTools.name: MacroStringTools
haxe.macro.MacroStringTools.description:
This class provides some utility methods to work with strings in macro
context.

haxe.macro.MacroType.name: MacroType
haxe.macro.MacroType.description:
This type is meant to be used to generate custom types using a macro.
For instance by doing MacroType<[my.Class.myMacro(55)]>

haxe.macro.Printer.name: Printer
haxe.macro.Printer.description:
This class provides some utility methods to convert elements from the
macro context to a human-readable String representation.

haxe.macro.TypeTools.name: TypeTools
haxe.macro.TypeTools.description:
This class provides some utility methods to work with types. It is
best used through 'using haxe.macro.TypeTools' syntax and then provides
additional methods on haxe.macro.Type instances.

haxe.macro.TypedExprTools.name: TypedExprTools
haxe.macro.TypedExprTools.description:
This class provides some utility methods to work with typed expressions.
It is best used through 'using haxe.macro.TypedExprTools' syntax and then
provides additional methods on haxe.macro.TypedExpr instances.

haxe.macro.AnonStatus.name: AnonStatus
haxe.macro.AnonStatus.description: Represents the kind of the anonymous structure type.

haxe.macro.ClassKind.name: ClassKind
haxe.macro.ClassKind.description: Represents the kind of a class.

haxe.macro.ComplexType.name: ComplexType
haxe.macro.ComplexType.description: Represents a type syntax in the AST.

haxe.macro.ExprDef.name: ExprDef
haxe.macro.ExprDef.description: Represents the kind of a node in the AST.

haxe.macro.FieldAccess.name: FieldAccess
haxe.macro.FieldAccess.description: Represents the kind of field access in the typed AST.

haxe.macro.FieldType.name: FieldType
haxe.macro.FieldType.description: Represents the field type in the AST.

haxe.macro.FunctionKind.name: FunctionKind
haxe.macro.FunctionKind.description: Represents function kind in the AST

haxe.macro.ModuleType.name: ModuleType
haxe.macro.ModuleType.description:
Represents a module type. These are the types that can be declared in a Haxe
module and which are passed to the generators (except TTypeDecl).

haxe.macro.QuoteStatus.name: QuoteStatus
haxe.macro.QuoteStatus.description: Represents the way something is quoted.

haxe.macro.TypeParam.name: TypeParam
haxe.macro.TypeParam.description: Represents a concrete type parameter in the AST.

haxe.macro.TypedExprDef.name: TypedExprDef
haxe.macro.TypedExprDef.description: Represents kind of a node in the typed AST.

haxe.macro.AnonType.name: AnonType
haxe.macro.AnonType.description: Represents information for anonymous structure types.

haxe.macro.BaseType.name: BaseType
haxe.macro.BaseType.description:
The information that all types (ClassType, EnumType, DefType,
AbstractType) have in common.

haxe.macro.Catch.name: Catch
haxe.macro.Catch.description: Represents a catch in the AST.

haxe.macro.Expr.name: Expr
haxe.macro.Expr.description: Represents a node in the AST.

haxe.macro.ExprOf.name: ExprOf
haxe.macro.ExprOf.description:
Represents a AST node identical to Expr, but it allows constraining the
type of accepted expressions.

haxe.macro.Field.name: Field
haxe.macro.Field.description: Represents a field in the AST.

haxe.macro.Function.name: Function
haxe.macro.Function.description: Represents a function in the AST.

haxe.macro.FunctionArg.name: FunctionArg
haxe.macro.FunctionArg.description: Represents a function argument in the AST.

haxe.macro.JSGenApi.name: JSGenApi
haxe.macro.JSGenApi.description: This is the api that is passed to the custom JS generator.

haxe.macro.MetaAccess.name: MetaAccess
haxe.macro.MetaAccess.description:
MetaAccess is a wrapper for the Metadata array. It can be used to add
metadata to and remove metadata from its origin.

haxe.macro.MetadataEntry.name: MetadataEntry
haxe.macro.MetadataEntry.description: Represents a metadata entry in the AST.

haxe.macro.ObjectField.name: ObjectField
haxe.macro.ObjectField.description: Represents the field of an object declaration.

haxe.macro.Position.name: Position
haxe.macro.Position.description: Represents a position in a file.

haxe.macro.Ref.name: Ref
haxe.macro.Ref.description:
Represents a reference to internal compiler structure. It exists to avoid
expensive encoding if it is not required and to ensure that physical
equality remains intact.

haxe.macro.TFunc.name: TFunc
haxe.macro.TFunc.description: Represents a function in the typed AST.

haxe.macro.TVar.name: TVar
haxe.macro.TVar.description: Represents a variable in the typed AST.

haxe.macro.TypeParamDecl.name: TypeParamDecl
haxe.macro.TypeParamDecl.description: Represents a type parameter declaration in the AST.

haxe.macro.TypeParameter.name: TypeParameter
haxe.macro.TypeParameter.description: Represents the declaration of type parameters.

haxe.macro.TypePath.name: TypePath
haxe.macro.TypePath.description: Represents a type path in the AST.

haxe.macro.Var.name: Var
haxe.macro.Var.description: Represents a variable in the AST.

haxe.rtti.CTypeTools.name: CTypeTools
haxe.rtti.CTypeTools.description:
The CTypeTools class contains some extra functionalities for handling
CType instances.

haxe.rtti.Meta.name: Meta
haxe.rtti.Meta.description: An API to access classes and enums metadata at runtime.

haxe.rtti.Rtti.name: Rtti
haxe.rtti.Rtti.description: Rtti is a helper class which supplements the @:rtti metadata.

haxe.rtti.TypeApi.name: TypeApi
haxe.rtti.TypeApi.description: Contains type and equality checks functionalities for RTTI.

haxe.rtti.XmlParser.name: XmlParser
haxe.rtti.XmlParser.description:
XmlParser processes the runtime type information (RTTI) which
is stored as a XML string in a static field __rtti.

haxe.rtti.Rights.name: Rights
haxe.rtti.Rights.description: Represents the runtime rights of a type.

haxe.rtti.TypeTree.name: TypeTree
haxe.rtti.TypeTree.description: The tree types of the runtime type.

haxe.rtti.FunctionArgument.name: FunctionArgument
haxe.rtti.FunctionArgument.description: The function argument runtime type information.

haxe.rtti.PathParams.name: PathParams
haxe.rtti.PathParams.description: The type parameters in the runtime type information.

haxe.rtti.Platforms.name: Platforms
haxe.rtti.Platforms.description: A list of strings representing the targets where the type is available.

haxe.rtti.TypeParams.name: TypeParams
haxe.rtti.TypeParams.description:
An array of strings representing the names of the type parameters the type
has. As of Haxe 3.2.0, this does not include the constraints.

haxe.xml.Printer.name: Printer
haxe.xml.Printer.description:
This class provides utility methods to convert Xml instances to
String representation.

haxe.xml.Access.name: Access
haxe.xml.Access.description:
The haxe.xml.Access API helps providing a fast dot-syntax access to the
most common Xml methods.

haxe.zip.InflateImpl.name: InflateImpl
haxe.zip.InflateImpl.description: A pure Haxe implementation of the ZLIB Inflate algorithm which allows reading compressed data without any platform-specific support.

java.internal.Function.name: Function
java.internal.Function.description:
These classes are automatically generated by the compiler. They are only
here so there is an option for e.g. defining them as externs if you are compiling
in modules (untested)

java.internal.Runtime.name: Runtime
java.internal.Runtime.description:
This class is meant for internal compiler use only. It provides the Haxe runtime
compatibility to the host language. Do not access it directly.

js.html.AbortController.name: AbortController
js.html.AbortController.description: The AbortController interface represents a controller object that allows you to abort one or more DOM requests as and when desired.

js.html.AbortSignal.name: AbortSignal
js.html.AbortSignal.description: The AbortSignal interface represents a signal object that allows you to communicate with a DOM request (such as a Fetch) and abort it if required via an AbortController object.

js.html.AnchorElement.name: AnchorElement
js.html.AnchorElement.description: The HTMLAnchorElement interface represents hyperlink elements and provides special properties and methods (beyond those of the regular HTMLElement object interface that they inherit from) for manipulating the layout and presentation of such elements.

js.html.Animation.name: Animation
js.html.Animation.description: The Animation interface of the Web Animations API represents a single animation player and provides playback controls and a timeline for an animation node or source.

js.html.AnimationEffect.name: AnimationEffect
js.html.AnimationEffect.description: The AnimationEffect interface of the Web Animations API defines current and future animation effects like KeyframeEffect, which can be passed to Animation objects for playing, and KeyframeEffectReadOnly (which is used by CSS Animations and Transitions).

js.html.AnimationEvent.name: AnimationEvent
js.html.AnimationEvent.description: The AnimationEvent interface represents events providing information related to animations.

js.html.AnimationPlaybackEvent.name: AnimationPlaybackEvent
js.html.AnimationPlaybackEvent.description: The AnimationPlaybackEvent interface of the Web Animations API represents animation events.

js.html.AnimationTimeline.name: AnimationTimeline
js.html.AnimationTimeline.description: The AnimationTimeline interface of the Web Animations API represents the timeline of an animation. This interface exists to define timeline features (inherited by DocumentTimeline and future timeline types) and is not itself directly used by developers. Anywhere you see AnimationTimeline, you should use DocumentTimeline or any other timeline type instead.

js.html.AreaElement.name: AreaElement
js.html.AreaElement.description: The HTMLAreaElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond those of the regular object HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of area elements.

js.html.Attr.name: Attr
js.html.Attr.description: This type represents a DOM element's attribute as an object. In most DOM methods, you will probably directly retrieve the attribute as a string (e.g., Element.getAttribute(), but certain functions (e.g., Element.getAttributeNode()) or means of iterating give Attr types.

js.html.AudioElement.name: AudioElement
js.html.AudioElement.description: The HTMLAudioElement interface provides access to the properties of audio elements, as well as methods to manipulate them. It derives from the HTMLMediaElement interface.

js.html.AudioTrack.name: AudioTrack
js.html.AudioTrack.description: The AudioTrack interface represents a single audio track from one of the HTML media elements, audio or video.

js.html.AudioTrackList.name: AudioTrackList
js.html.AudioTrackList.description: The AudioTrackList interface is used to represent a list of the audio tracks contained within a given HTML media element, with each track represented by a separate AudioTrack object in the list.

js.html.BRElement.name: BRElement
js.html.BRElement.description: The HTMLBRElement interface represents a HTML line break element (br). It inherits from HTMLElement.

js.html.BaseElement.name: BaseElement
js.html.BaseElement.description: The HTMLBaseElement interface contains the base URI for a document. This object inherits all of the properties and methods as described in the HTMLElement interface.

js.html.BatteryManager.name: BatteryManager
js.html.BatteryManager.description: The BatteryManager interface provides ways to get information about the system's battery charge level.

js.html.BeforeUnloadEvent.name: BeforeUnloadEvent
js.html.BeforeUnloadEvent.description: The beforeunload event is fired when the window, the document and its resources are about to be unloaded.

js.html.Blob.name: Blob
js.html.Blob.description: A Blob object represents a file-like object of immutable, raw data. Blobs represent data that isn't necessarily in a JavaScript-native format. The File interface is based on Blob, inheriting blob functionality and expanding it to support files on the user's system.

js.html.BlobEvent.name: BlobEvent
js.html.BlobEvent.description: The BlobEvent interface represents events associated with a Blob. These blobs are typically, but not necessarily,  associated with media content.

js.html.BodyElement.name: BodyElement
js.html.BodyElement.description: The HTMLBodyElement interface provides special properties (beyond those of the regular HTMLElement interface they also inherit) for manipulating body elements.

js.html.BroadcastChannel.name: BroadcastChannel
js.html.BroadcastChannel.description: The BroadcastChannel interface represents a named channel that any browsing context of a given origin can subscribe to. It allows communication between different documents (in different windows, tabs, frames or iframes) of the same origin. Messages are broadcasted via a message event fired at all BroadcastChannel objects listening to the channel.

js.html.ButtonElement.name: ButtonElement
js.html.ButtonElement.description: The HTMLButtonElement interface provides properties and methods (beyond the button object interface it also has available to them by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of button elements.

js.html.CDATASection.name: CDATASection
js.html.CDATASection.description: The CDATASection interface represents a CDATA section that can be used within XML to include extended portions of unescaped text. The symbols  and &amp; don’t need escaping as they normally do when inside a CDATA section.

js.html.CSS.name: CSS
js.html.CSS.description: The CSS interface holds useful CSS-related methods. No object with this interface are implemented: it contains only static methods and therefore is a utilitarian interface.

js.html.CSSConditionRule.name: CSSConditionRule
js.html.CSSConditionRule.description: An object implementing the CSSConditionRule interface represents a single condition CSS at-rule, which consists of a condition and a statement block. It is a child of CSSGroupingRule.

js.html.CSSCounterStyleRule.name: CSSCounterStyleRule
js.html.CSSCounterStyleRule.description: The CSSCounterStyleRule interface represents an @counter-style at-rule.

js.html.CSSGroupingRule.name: CSSGroupingRule
js.html.CSSGroupingRule.description: An object implementing the CSSGroupingRule interface represents any CSS at-rule that contains other rules nested within it.

js.html.CSSKeyframeRule.name: CSSKeyframeRule
js.html.CSSKeyframeRule.description: The CSSKeyframeRule interface describes an object representing a set of style for a given keyframe. It corresponds to the contains of a single keyframe of a @keyframes at-rule. It implements the CSSRule interface with a type value of 8 (CSSRule.KEYFRAME_RULE).

js.html.CSSKeyframesRule.name: CSSKeyframesRule
js.html.CSSKeyframesRule.description: The CSSKeyframesRule interface describes an object representing a complete set of keyframes for a CSS animation. It corresponds to the contains of a whole @keyframes at-rule. It implements the CSSRule interface with a type value of 7 (CSSRule.KEYFRAMES_RULE).

js.html.CSSMediaRule.name: CSSMediaRule
js.html.CSSMediaRule.description: The CSSMediaRule is an interface representing a single CSS @media rule. It implements the CSSConditionRule interface, and therefore the CSSGroupingRule and the CSSRule interface with a type value of 4 (CSSRule.MEDIA_RULE).

js.html.CSSNamespaceRule.name: CSSNamespaceRule
js.html.CSSNamespaceRule.description: The CSSNamespaceRule interface describes an object representing a single CSS @namespace at-rule. It implements the CSSRule interface, with a type value of 10 (CSSRule.NAMESPACE_RULE).

js.html.CSSPageRule.name: CSSPageRule
js.html.CSSPageRule.description: CSSPageRule is an interface representing a single CSS @page rule. It implements the CSSRule interface with a type value of 6 (CSSRule.PAGE_RULE).

js.html.CSSRule.name: CSSRule
js.html.CSSRule.description: The CSSRule interface represents a single CSS rule. There are several types of rules, listed in the Type constants section below.

js.html.CSSRuleList.name: CSSRuleList
js.html.CSSRuleList.description: A CSSRuleList is an (indirect-modify only) array-like object containing an ordered collection of CSSRule objects.

js.html.CSSStyleDeclaration.name: CSSStyleDeclaration
js.html.CSSStyleDeclaration.description: CSSStyleDeclaration represents a collection of CSS property-value pairs. It is used in a few APIs:

js.html.CSSStyleRule.name: CSSStyleRule
js.html.CSSStyleRule.description: CSSStyleRule represents a single CSS style rule. It implements the CSSRule interface with a type value of 1 (CSSRule.STYLE_RULE).

js.html.CSSStyleSheet.name: CSSStyleSheet
js.html.CSSStyleSheet.description: The CSSStyleSheet interface represents a single CSS style sheet. It inherits properties and methods from its parent, StyleSheet.

js.html.CSSSupportsRule.name: CSSSupportsRule
js.html.CSSSupportsRule.description: The CSSSupportsRule interface describes an object representing a single CSS @supports at-rule. It implements the CSSConditionRule interface, and therefore the CSSRule and CSSGroupingRule interfaces with a type value of 12 (CSSRule.SUPPORTS_RULE).

js.html.Cache.name: Cache
js.html.Cache.description: The Cache interface provides a storage mechanism for Request / Response object pairs that are cached, for example as part of the ServiceWorker life cycle. Note that the Cache interface is exposed to windowed scopes as well as workers. You don't have to use it in conjunction with service workers, even though it is defined in the service worker spec.

js.html.CacheStorage.name: CacheStorage
js.html.CacheStorage.description: The CacheStorage interface represents the storage for Cache objects.

js.html.CanvasElement.name: CanvasElement
js.html.CanvasElement.description: The HTMLCanvasElement interface provides properties and methods for manipulating the layout and presentation of canvas elements. The HTMLCanvasElement interface also inherits the properties and methods of the HTMLElement interface.

js.html.CanvasGradient.name: CanvasGradient
js.html.CanvasGradient.description: The CanvasGradient interface represents an opaque object describing a gradient. It is returned by the methods CanvasRenderingContext2D.createLinearGradient() or CanvasRenderingContext2D.createRadialGradient().

js.html.CanvasPattern.name: CanvasPattern
js.html.CanvasPattern.description: The CanvasPattern interface represents an opaque object describing a pattern, based on an image, a canvas, or a video, created by the CanvasRenderingContext2D.createPattern() method.

js.html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.name: CanvasRenderingContext2D
js.html.CanvasRenderingContext2D.description: To get an object of this interface, call getContext() on a canvas element, supplying "2d" as the argument:

js.html.CaretPosition.name: CaretPosition
js.html.CaretPosition.description: The CaretPosition interface represents the caret postion, an indicator for the text insertion point. You can get a CaretPosition using the document.caretPositionFromPoint method.

js.html.CharacterData.name: CharacterData
js.html.CharacterData.description: The CharacterData abstract interface represents a Node object that contains characters. This is an abstract interface, meaning there aren't any object of type CharacterData: it is implemented by other interfaces, like Text, '. In XML, the character sequence '--' cannot be used within a comment.">Comment, or ProcessingInstruction which aren't abstract.

js.html.Client.name: Client
js.html.Client.description: The Client interface represents an executable context such as a Worker, or a SharedWorker. Window clients are represented by the more-specific WindowClient. You can get Client/WindowClient objects from methods such as Clients.matchAll() and Clients.get().

js.html.Clients.name: Clients
js.html.Clients.description: The Clients interface provides access to Client objects. Access it via self.clients within a service worker.

js.html.Clipboard.name: Clipboard
js.html.Clipboard.description: The Clipboard interface implements the Clipboard API, providing—if the user grants permission—both read and write access to the contents of the system clipboard.

js.html.ClipboardEvent.name: ClipboardEvent
js.html.ClipboardEvent.description: The ClipboardEvent interface represents events providing information related to modification of the clipboard, that is cut, copy, and paste events.

js.html.CloseEvent.name: CloseEvent
js.html.CloseEvent.description: A CloseEvent is sent to clients using WebSockets when the connection is closed. This is delivered to the listener indicated by the WebSocket object's onclose attribute.

js.html.Comment.name: Comment
js.html.Comment.description: The Comment interface represents textual notations within markup; although it is generally not visually shown, such comments are available to be read in the source view. Comments are represented in HTML and XML as content between '!--' and '--'. In XML, the character sequence '--' cannot be used within a comment.

js.html.CompositionEvent.name: CompositionEvent
js.html.CompositionEvent.description: The DOM CompositionEvent represents events that occur due to the user indirectly entering text.

js.html.Console.name: Console
js.html.Console.description: The Console object provides access to the browser's debugging console (e.g. the Web Console in Firefox). The specifics of how it works varies from browser to browser, but there is a de facto set of features that are typically provided.

js.html.ConsoleInstance.name: ConsoleInstance
js.html.ConsoleInstance.description: The Console object provides access to the browser's debugging console (e.g. the Web Console in Firefox). The specifics of how it works varies from browser to browser, but there is a de facto set of features that are typically provided.

js.html.Crypto.name: Crypto
js.html.Crypto.description: The Crypto interface represents basic cryptography features available in the current context. It allows access to a cryptographically strong random number generator and to cryptographic primitives.

js.html.CryptoKey.name: CryptoKey
js.html.CryptoKey.description: The CryptoKey interface represents a cryptographic key derived from a specific key algorithm.

js.html.CustomEvent.name: CustomEvent
js.html.CustomEvent.description: This interface inherits properties from its parent, Event:

js.html.DListElement.name: DListElement
js.html.DListElement.description: The HTMLDListElement interface provides special properties (beyond those of the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating definition list elements.

js.html.DOMElement.name: DOMElement
js.html.DOMElement.description: Element is the most general base class from which all objects in a Document inherit. It only has methods and properties common to all kinds of elements. More specific classes inherit from Element.

js.html.DOMError.name: DOMError
js.html.DOMError.description: The DOMError interface describes an error object that contains an error name.

js.html.DOMException.name: DOMException
js.html.DOMException.description: The DOMException interface represents an abnormal event (called an exception) which occurs as a result of calling a method or accessing a property of a web API.

js.html.DOMImplementation.name: DOMImplementation
js.html.DOMImplementation.description: The DOMImplementation interface represent an object providing methods which are not dependent on any particular document. Such an object is returned by the Document.implementation property.

js.html.DOMMatrix.name: DOMMatrix
js.html.DOMMatrix.description: The DOMMatrix interface represents 4x4 matrices, suitable for 2D and 3D operations.

js.html.DOMMatrixReadOnly.name: DOMMatrixReadOnly
js.html.DOMMatrixReadOnly.description: The DOMMatrixReadOnly interface represents 4x4 matrices, suitable for 2D and 3D operations. If this interface defines only read-only matrices, the DOMMatrix interface which inherits from it, add all the properties and the methods to allow to have modifiable matrices.

js.html.DOMParser.name: DOMParser
js.html.DOMParser.description: The DOMParser interface provides the ability to parse XML or HTML source code from a string into a DOM Document.

js.html.DOMPoint.name: DOMPoint
js.html.DOMPoint.description: A DOMPoint object represents a 2D or 3D point in a coordinate system; it includes values for the coordinates in up to three dimensions, as well as an optional perspective value.

js.html.DOMPointReadOnly.name: DOMPointReadOnly
js.html.DOMPointReadOnly.description: The DOMPointReadOnly interface specifies the coordinate and perspective fields used by DOMPoint to define a 2D or 3D point in a coordinate system.

js.html.DOMQuad.name: DOMQuad
js.html.DOMQuad.description: A DOMQuad is a collection of four DOMPoints defining the corners of an arbitrary quadrilateral. Returning DOMQuads lets getBoxQuads() return accurate information even when arbitrary 2D or 3D transforms are present. It has a handy bounds attribute returning a DOMRectReadOnly for those cases where you just want an axis-aligned bounding rectangle.

js.html.DOMRectReadOnly.name: DOMRectReadOnly
js.html.DOMRectReadOnly.description: The DOMRectReadOnly interface specifies the standard properties used by DOMRect to define a rectangle.

js.html.DOMStringList.name: DOMStringList
js.html.DOMStringList.description: A type returned by some APIs which contains a list of DOMString (strings).

js.html.DOMStringMap.name: DOMStringMap
js.html.DOMStringMap.description: Used by the dataset HTML attribute to represent data for custom attributes added to elements.

js.html.DOMTokenList.name: DOMTokenList
js.html.DOMTokenList.description: The DOMTokenList interface represents a set of space-separated tokens. Such a set is returned by Element.classList, HTMLLinkElement.relList, HTMLAnchorElement.relList, HTMLAreaElement.relList, HTMLIframeElement.sandbox, or HTMLOutputElement.htmlFor. It is indexed beginning with 0 as with JavaScript Array objects. DOMTokenList is always case-sensitive.

js.html.DataElement.name: DataElement
js.html.DataElement.description: The HTMLDataElement interface provides special properties (beyond the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating data elements.

js.html.DataListElement.name: DataListElement
js.html.DataListElement.description: The HTMLDataListElement interface provides special properties (beyond the HTMLElement object interface it also has available to it by inheritance) to manipulate datalist elements and their content.

js.html.DataTransfer.name: DataTransfer
js.html.DataTransfer.description: The DataTransfer object is used to hold the data that is being dragged during a drag and drop operation. It may hold one or more data items, each of one or more data types. For more information about drag and drop, see HTML Drag and Drop API.

js.html.DataTransferItem.name: DataTransferItem
js.html.DataTransferItem.description: The DataTransferItem object represents one drag data item. During a drag operation, each drag event has a dataTransfer property which contains a list of drag data items. Each item in the list is a DataTransferItem object.

js.html.DataTransferItemList.name: DataTransferItemList
js.html.DataTransferItemList.description: The DataTransferItemList object is a list of DataTransferItem objects representing items being dragged. During a drag operation, each DragEvent has a dataTransfer property and that property is a DataTransferItemList.

js.html.DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope.name: DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope
js.html.DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope.description: The DedicatedWorkerGlobalScope object (the Worker global scope) is accessible through the self keyword. Some additional global functions, namespaces objects, and constructors, not typically associated with the worker global scope, but available on it, are listed in the JavaScript Reference. See also: Functions available to workers.

js.html.DetailsElement.name: DetailsElement
js.html.DetailsElement.description: The HTMLDetailsElement interface provides special properties (beyond the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating details elements.

js.html.DeviceMotionEvent.name: DeviceMotionEvent
js.html.DeviceMotionEvent.description: The DeviceMotionEvent provides web developers with information about the speed of changes for the device's position and orientation.

js.html.DeviceOrientationEvent.name: DeviceOrientationEvent
js.html.DeviceOrientationEvent.description: The DeviceOrientationEvent provides web developers with information from the physical orientation of the device running the web page.

js.html.DivElement.name: DivElement
js.html.DivElement.description: The HTMLDivElement interface provides special properties (beyond the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating div elements.

js.html.Document.name: Document
js.html.Document.description: The Document interface represents any web page loaded in the browser and serves as an entry point into the web page's content, which is the DOM tree.HTMLElement

js.html.DocumentFragment.name: DocumentFragment
js.html.DocumentFragment.description: The DocumentFragment interface represents a minimal document object that has no parent. It is used as a lightweight version of Document that stores a segment of a document structure comprised of nodes just like a standard document. The key difference is that because the document fragment isn't part of the active document tree structure, changes made to the fragment don't affect the document, cause reflow, or incur any performance impact that can occur when changes are made.

js.html.DocumentTimeline.name: DocumentTimeline
js.html.DocumentTimeline.description: The DocumentTimeline interface of the the Web Animations API represents animation timelines, including the default document timeline (accessed via Document.timeline).

js.html.DocumentType.name: DocumentType
js.html.DocumentType.description: The DocumentType interface represents a Node containing a doctype.

js.html.DragEvent.name: DragEvent
js.html.DragEvent.description: The DragEvent interface is a DOM event that represents a drag and drop interaction. The user initiates a drag by placing a pointer device (such as a mouse) on the touch surface and then dragging the pointer to a new location (such as another DOM element). Applications are free to interpret a drag and drop interaction in an application-specific way.

js.html.Element.name: Element
js.html.Element.description: The HTMLElement interface represents any HTML element. Some elements directly implement this interface, others implement it via an interface that inherits it.

js.html.EmbedElement.name: EmbedElement
js.html.EmbedElement.description: The HTMLEmbedElement interface, which provides special properties (beyond the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating embed elements.

js.html.ErrorEvent.name: ErrorEvent
js.html.ErrorEvent.description: The ErrorEvent interface represents events providing information related to errors in scripts or in files.

js.html.Event.name: Event
js.html.Event.description: The Event interface represents any event which takes place in the DOM; some are user-generated (such as mouse or keyboard events), while others are generated by APIs (such as events that indicate an animation has finished running, a video has been paused, and so forth). There are many types of events, some of which use other interfaces based on the main Event interface. Event itself contains the properties and methods which are common to all events.

js.html.EventSource.name: EventSource
js.html.EventSource.description: The EventSource interface is web content's interface to server-sent events. An EventSource instance opens a persistent connection to an HTTP server, which sends events in text/event-stream format.

js.html.EventTarget.name: EventTarget
js.html.EventTarget.description: EventTarget is an interface implemented by objects that can receive events and may have listeners for them.

js.html.ExtendableEvent.name: ExtendableEvent
js.html.ExtendableEvent.description: The ExtendableEvent interface extends the lifetime of the install and activate events dispatched on the global scope as part of the service worker lifecycle. This ensures that any functional events (like FetchEvent) are not dispatched until it upgrades database schemas and deletes the outdated cache entries.

js.html.ExtendableMessageEvent.name: ExtendableMessageEvent
js.html.ExtendableMessageEvent.description: The ExtendableMessageEvent interface of the ServiceWorker API represents the event object of a message event fired on a service worker (when a channel message is received on the ServiceWorkerGlobalScope from another context) — extends the lifetime of such events.

js.html.FetchEvent.name: FetchEvent
js.html.FetchEvent.description: This is the event type for fetch events dispatched on the service worker global scope. It contains information about the fetch, including the request and how the receiver will treat the response. It provides the event.respondWith() method, which allows us to provide a response to this fetch.

js.html.FieldSetElement.name: FieldSetElement
js.html.FieldSetElement.description: The HTMLFieldSetElement interface has special properties and methods (beyond the regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of field-set elements.

js.html.File.name: File
js.html.File.description: The File interface provides information about files and allows JavaScript in a web page to access their content.

js.html.FileList.name: FileList
js.html.FileList.description: An object of this type is returned by the files property of the HTML input element; this lets you access the list of files selected with the input type="file" element. It's also used for a list of files dropped into web content when using the drag and drop API; see the DataTransfer object for details on this usage.

js.html.FileReader.name: FileReader
js.html.FileReader.description: The FileReader object lets web applications asynchronously read the contents of files (or raw data buffers) stored on the user's computer, using File or Blob objects to specify the file or data to read.

js.html.FileReaderSync.name: FileReaderSync
js.html.FileReaderSync.description: The FileReaderSync interface allows to read File or Blob objects in a synchronous way.

js.html.FileSystem.name: FileSystem
js.html.FileSystem.description: The File and Directory Entries API interface FileSystem is used to represent a file system. These objects can be obtained from the filesystem property on any file system entry. Some browsers offer additional APIs to create and manage file systems, such as Chrome's requestFileSystem() method.

js.html.FileSystemDirectoryEntry.name: FileSystemDirectoryEntry
js.html.FileSystemDirectoryEntry.description: The FileSystemDirectoryEntry interface of the File and Directory Entries API represents a directory in a file system. It provides methods which make it possible to access and manipulate the files in a directory, as well as to access the entries within the directory.

js.html.FileSystemDirectoryReader.name: FileSystemDirectoryReader
js.html.FileSystemDirectoryReader.description: The FileSystemDirectoryReader interface of the File and Directory Entries API lets you access the FileEntry-based objects (generally FileSystemFileEntry or FileSystemDirectoryEntry) representing each entry in a directory.

js.html.FileSystemEntry.name: FileSystemEntry
js.html.FileSystemEntry.description: The FileSystemEntry interface of the File and Directory Entries API represents a single in a file system. The entry can be a file or a directory (directories are represented by the DirectoryEntry interface). It includes methods for working with files—including copying, moving, removing, and reading files—as well as information about a file it points to—including the file name and its path from the root to the entry.

js.html.FileSystemFileEntry.name: FileSystemFileEntry
js.html.FileSystemFileEntry.description: The FileSystemFileEntry interface of the File System API represents a file in a file system. It offers properties describing the file's attributes, as well as the file() method, which creates a File object that can be used to read the file.

js.html.FocusEvent.name: FocusEvent
js.html.FocusEvent.description: The FocusEvent interface represents focus-related events like focus, blur, focusin, or focusout.

js.html.FontElement.name: FontElement
js.html.FontElement.description: Implements the document object model (DOM) representation of the font element. The HTML Font Element font defines the font size, font face and color of text.

js.html.FontFace.name: FontFace
js.html.FontFace.description: The FontFace interface represents a single usable font face. It allows control of the source of the font face, being a URL to an external resource, or a buffer; it also allows control of when the font face is loaded and its current status.

js.html.FontFaceSet.name: FontFaceSet
js.html.FontFaceSet.description: The FontFaceSet interface of the CSS Font Loading API manages the loading of font-faces and querying of their download status.

js.html.FontFaceSetLoadEvent.name: FontFaceSetLoadEvent
js.html.FontFaceSetLoadEvent.description: The FontFaceSetLoadEvent interface of the the Css Font Loading API is fired whenever a FontFaceSet loads.

js.html.FormData.name: FormData
js.html.FormData.description: The FormData interface provides a way to easily construct a set of key/value pairs representing form fields and their values, which can then be easily sent using the XMLHttpRequest.send() method. It uses the same format a form would use if the encoding type were set to "multipart/form-data".

js.html.FormElement.name: FormElement
js.html.FormElement.description: The HTMLFormElement interface represents a form element in the DOM; it allows access to and in some cases modification of aspects of the form, as well as access to its component elements.

js.html.FrameSetElement.name: FrameSetElement
js.html.FrameSetElement.description: The HTMLFrameSetElement interface provides special properties (beyond those of the regular HTMLElement interface they also inherit) for manipulating frameset elements.

js.html.Gamepad.name: Gamepad
js.html.Gamepad.description: The Gamepad interface of the Gamepad API defines an individual gamepad or other controller, allowing access to information such as button presses, axis positions, and id.

js.html.GamepadButton.name: GamepadButton
js.html.GamepadButton.description: The GamepadButton interface defines an individual button of a gamepad or other controller, allowing access to the current state of different types of buttons available on the control device.

js.html.GamepadEvent.name: GamepadEvent
js.html.GamepadEvent.description: The GamepadEvent interface of the Gamepad API contains references to gamepads connected to the system, which is what the gamepad events Window.gamepadconnected and Window.gamepaddisconnected are fired in response to.

js.html.HRElement.name: HRElement
js.html.HRElement.description: The HTMLHRElement interface provides special properties (beyond those of the HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating hr elements.

js.html.HTMLCollection.name: HTMLCollection
js.html.HTMLCollection.description: The HTMLCollection interface represents a generic collection (array-like object similar to arguments) of elements (in document order) and offers methods and properties for selecting from the list.

js.html.HTMLDocument.name: HTMLDocument
js.html.HTMLDocument.description: HTMLDocument is an abstract interface which extends the Document interface to add HTML-specific features to the document object. It represents the root of the HTML document, within which its entire DOM hierarchy resides.

js.html.HTMLFormControlsCollection.name: HTMLFormControlsCollection
js.html.HTMLFormControlsCollection.description: The HTMLFormControlsCollection interface represents a collection of HTML form control elements.

js.html.HTMLOptionsCollection.name: HTMLOptionsCollection
js.html.HTMLOptionsCollection.description: HTMLOptionsCollection is an interface representing a collection of HTML option elements (in document order) and offers methods and properties for traversing the list as well as optionally altering its items. This type is returned solely by the "options" property of select.

js.html.HashChangeEvent.name: HashChangeEvent
js.html.HashChangeEvent.description: The HashChangeEvent event is fired when the fragment identifier of the URL has changed (the part of the URL that follows the # symbol, including the # symbol).

js.html.HeadElement.name: HeadElement
js.html.HeadElement.description: The HTMLHeadElement interface contains the descriptive information, or metadata, for a document. This object inherits all of the properties and methods described in the HTMLElement interface.

js.html.Headers.name: Headers
js.html.Headers.description: The Headers interface of the Fetch API allows you to perform various actions on HTTP request and response headers. These actions include retrieving, setting, adding to, and removing. A Headers object has an associated header list, which is initially empty and consists of zero or more name and value pairs.  You can add to this using methods like append() (see Examples.) In all methods of this interface, header names are matched by case-insensitive byte sequence.

js.html.HeadingElement.name: HeadingElement
js.html.HeadingElement.description: The HTMLHeadingElement interface represents the different heading elements. It inherits methods and properties from the HTMLElement interface.

js.html.History.name: History
js.html.History.description: The History interface allows manipulation of the browser session history, that is the pages visited in the tab or frame that the current page is loaded in.

js.html.HtmlElement.name: HtmlElement
js.html.HtmlElement.description: The HTMLHtmlElement interface serves as the root node for a given HTML document.  This object inherits the properties and methods described in the HTMLElement interface.

js.html.IFrameElement.name: IFrameElement
js.html.IFrameElement.description: The HTMLIFrameElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond those of the HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of inline frame elements.

js.html.ImageBitmap.name: ImageBitmap
js.html.ImageBitmap.description: The ImageBitmap interface represents a bitmap image which can be drawn to a canvas without undue latency. It can be created from a variety of source objects using the createImageBitmap() factory method. ImageBitmap provides an asynchronous and resource efficient pathway to prepare textures for rendering in WebGL.

js.html.ImageBitmapRenderingContext.name: ImageBitmapRenderingContext
js.html.ImageBitmapRenderingContext.description: The ImageBitmapRenderingContext interface is a canvas rendering context which only provides the functionality to replace the canvas's contents with the given ImageBitmap. Its context id (the first argument to HTMLCanvasElement.getContext() or OffscreenCanvas.getContext()  is "bitmaprenderer".

js.html.ImageCapture.name: ImageCapture
js.html.ImageCapture.description: The ImageCapture interface of the MediaStream Image Capture API provides an interface for capturing images from a photographic device referenced through a valid MediaStreamTrack.

js.html.ImageData.name: ImageData
js.html.ImageData.description: The ImageData interface represents the underlying pixel data of an area of a canvas element. It is created using the ImageData() constructor or creator methods on the CanvasRenderingContext2D object associated with a canvas: createImageData() and getImageData(). It can also be used to set a part of the canvas by using putImageData().

js.html.ImageElement.name: ImageElement
js.html.ImageElement.description: The HTMLImageElement interface provides special properties and methods  for manipulating the layout and presentation of img elements.

js.html.InputElement.name: InputElement
js.html.InputElement.description: The HTMLInputElement interface provides special properties and methods for manipulating the layout and presentation of input elements.

js.html.InputEvent.name: InputEvent
js.html.InputEvent.description: The InputEvent interface represents an event notifying of editable content change.

js.html.IntersectionObserver.name: IntersectionObserver
js.html.IntersectionObserver.description: provides a way to asynchronously observe changes in the intersection of a target element with an ancestor element or with a top-level document's viewport.

js.html.IntersectionObserverEntry.name: IntersectionObserverEntry
js.html.IntersectionObserverEntry.description: The IntersectionObserverEntry interface of the Intersection Observer API describes the intersection between the target element and its root container at a specific moment of transition.

js.html.KeyboardEvent.name: KeyboardEvent
js.html.KeyboardEvent.description: KeyboardEvent objects describe a user interaction with the keyboard; each event describes a single interaction between the user and a key (or combination of a key with modifier keys) on the keyboard.

js.html.KeyframeEffect.name: KeyframeEffect
js.html.KeyframeEffect.description: The KeyframeEffect interface of the Web Animations API lets us create sets of animatable properties and values, called keyframes. These can then be played using the Animation() constructor.

js.html.LIElement.name: LIElement
js.html.LIElement.description: The HTMLLIElement interface exposes specific properties and methods (beyond those defined by regular HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating list elements.

js.html.LabelElement.name: LabelElement
js.html.LabelElement.description: The HTMLLabelElement interface gives access to properties specific to label elements. It inherits methods and properties from the base HTMLElement interface.

js.html.LegendElement.name: LegendElement
js.html.LegendElement.description: The HTMLLegendElement is an interface allowing to access properties of the legend elements. It inherits properties and methods from the HTMLElement interface.

js.html.LinkElement.name: LinkElement
js.html.LinkElement.description: The HTMLLinkElement interface represents reference information for external resources and the relationship of those resources to a document and vice-versa. This object inherits all of the properties and methods of the HTMLElement interface.

js.html.LocalMediaStream.name: LocalMediaStream
js.html.LocalMediaStream.description: The LocalMediaStream interface was part of the Media Capture and Streams API, representing a stream of data being generated locally (such as by getUserMedia(). However, getUserMedia() now returns a MediaStream instead, and this interface has been removed from the specification.

js.html.Location.name: Location
js.html.Location.description: The Location interface represents the location (URL) of the object it is linked to. Changes done on it are reflected on the object it relates to. Both the Document and Window interface have such a linked Location, accessible via Document.location and Window.location respectively.

js.html.MapElement.name: MapElement
js.html.MapElement.description: The HTMLMapElement interface provides special properties and methods (beyond those of the regular object HTMLElement interface it also has available to it by inheritance) for manipulating the layout and presentation of map elements.

js.html.MediaDeviceInfo.name: MediaDeviceInfo
js.html.MediaDeviceInfo.description: The MediaDevicesInfo interface contains information that describes a single media input or output device.

js.html.MediaDevices.name: MediaDevices
js.html.MediaDevices.description: The MediaDevices interface provides access to connected media input devices like cameras and microphones, as well as screen sharing. In essence, it lets you obtain access to any hardware source of media data.

js.html.MediaElement.name: MediaElement
js.html.MediaElement.description: The HTMLMediaElement interface adds to HTMLElement the properties and methods needed to support basic media-related capabilities that are common to audio and video.

js.html.MediaError.name: MediaError
js.html.MediaError.description: The MediaError interface represents an error which occurred while handling media in an HTML media element based on HTMLMediaElement, such as audio or video.

js.html.MediaQueryList.name: MediaQueryList
js.html.MediaQueryList.description: A MediaQueryList object stores information on a media query applied to a document, and handles sending notifications to listeners when the media query state change (i.e. when the media query test starts or stops evaluating to true).

js.html.MediaQueryListEvent.name: MediaQueryListEvent
js.html.MediaQueryListEvent.description: The MediaQueryListEvent object stores information on the changes that have happened to a MediaQueryList object — instances are available as the event object on a function referenced by a MediaQueryList.onchange property or MediaQueryList.addEvent() call.

js.html.MediaRecorder.name: MediaRecorder
js.html.MediaRecorder.description: The MediaRecorder interface of the MediaStream Recording API provides functionality to easily record media. It is created using the MediaRecorder() constructor.

js.html.MediaRecorderErrorEvent.name: MediaRecorderErrorEvent
