js.html.svg.AnimatedLengthList.description: The SVGAnimatedLengthList interface is used for attributes of type SVGLengthList which can be animated.

js.html.svg.AnimatedNumber.name: AnimatedNumber
js.html.svg.AnimatedNumber.description: The SVGAnimatedNumber interface is used for attributes of basic type Number which can be animated.

js.html.svg.AnimatedNumberList.name: AnimatedNumberList
js.html.svg.AnimatedNumberList.description: The SVGAnimatedNumber interface is used for attributes which take a list of numbers and which can be animated.

js.html.svg.AnimatedPreserveAspectRatio.name: AnimatedPreserveAspectRatio
js.html.svg.AnimatedPreserveAspectRatio.description: The SVGAnimatedPreserveAspectRatio interface is used for attributes of type SVGPreserveAspectRatio which can be animated.

js.html.svg.AnimatedRect.name: AnimatedRect
js.html.svg.AnimatedRect.description: The SVGAnimatedRect interface is used for attributes of basic SVGRect which can be animated.

js.html.svg.AnimatedString.name: AnimatedString
js.html.svg.AnimatedString.description: The SVGAnimatedString interface represents string attributes which can be animated from each SVG declaration. You need to create SVG attribute before doing anything else, everything should be declared inside this.

js.html.svg.AnimatedTransformList.name: AnimatedTransformList
js.html.svg.AnimatedTransformList.description: The SVGAnimatedTransformList interface is used for attributes which take a list of numbers and which can be animated.

js.html.svg.AnimationElement.name: AnimationElement
js.html.svg.AnimationElement.description: The SVGAnimationElement interface is the base interface for all of the animation element interfaces: SVGAnimateElement, SVGSetElement, SVGAnimateColorElement, SVGAnimateMotionElement and SVGAnimateTransformElement.

js.html.svg.CircleElement.name: CircleElement
js.html.svg.CircleElement.description: The SVGCircleElement interface is an interface for the circle element. The circle element is defined by the cx and cy attributes that denote the coordinates of the centre of the circle.

js.html.svg.ClipPathElement.name: ClipPathElement
js.html.svg.ClipPathElement.description: The SVGClipPathElement interface provides access to the properties of clipPath elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

js.html.svg.ComponentTransferFunctionEle.name: ComponentTransferFunctionElement
js.html.svg.ComponentTransferFunctionEle.description: The SVGComponentTransferFunctionElement interface defines a base interface used by the component transfer function interfaces.

js.html.svg.DefsElement.name: DefsElement
js.html.svg.DefsElement.description: The SVGDefsElement interface corresponds to the defs element.

js.html.svg.DescElement.name: DescElement

js.html.svg.Element.name: Element

js.html.svg.EllipseElement.name: EllipseElement
js.html.svg.EllipseElement.description: The SVGEllipseElement interface provides access to the properties of ellipse elements.

js.html.svg.FEMorphologyElement.name: FEMorphologyElement

js.html.svg.FEOffsetElement.name: FEOffsetElement

js.html.svg.FEPointLightElement.name: FEPointLightElement

js.html.svg.FESpecularLightingElement.name: FESpecularLightingElement
js.html.svg.FESpecularLightingElement.description: The SVGFESpecularLightingElement interface corresponds to the feSpecularLighting element.

js.html.svg.FESpotLightElement.name: FESpotLightElement
js.html.svg.FESpotLightElement.description: The SVGFESpotLightElement interface corresponds to the feSpotLight element.

js.html.svg.FETileElement.name: FETileElement
js.html.svg.FETileElement.description: The SVGFETileElement interface corresponds to the feTile element.

js.html.svg.FETurbulenceElement.name: FETurbulenceElement
js.html.svg.FETurbulenceElement.description: The SVGFETurbulenceElement interface corresponds to the feTurbulence element.

js.html.svg.FilterElement.name: FilterElement
js.html.svg.FilterElement.description: The SVGFilterElement interface provides access to the properties of filter elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

js.html.svg.ForeignObjectElement.name: ForeignObjectElement
js.html.svg.ForeignObjectElement.description: The SVGForeignObjectElement interface provides access to the properties of foreignObject elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

js.html.svg.GElement.name: GElement
js.html.svg.GElement.description: The SVGGElement interface corresponds to the g element.

js.html.svg.GeometryElement.name: GeometryElement
js.html.svg.GeometryElement.description: The SVGGeometryElement interface represents SVG elements whose rendering is defined by geometry with an equivalent path, and which can be filled and stroked. This includes paths and the basic shapes.

js.html.svg.GradientElement.name: GradientElement
js.html.svg.GradientElement.description: The SVGGradient interface is a base interface used by SVGLinearGradientElement and SVGRadialGradientElement.

js.html.svg.GraphicsElement.name: GraphicsElement
js.html.svg.GraphicsElement.description: The SVGGraphicsElement interface represents SVG elements whose primary purpose is to directly render graphics into a group.

js.html.svg.ImageElement.name: ImageElement
js.html.svg.ImageElement.description: The SVGImageElement interface corresponds to the image element.

js.html.svg.Length.name: Length
js.html.svg.Length.description: The SVGLength interface correspond to the length basic data type.

js.html.svg.LengthList.name: LengthList
js.html.svg.LengthList.description: The SVGLengthList defines a list of SVGLength objects.

js.html.svg.LineElement.name: LineElement
js.html.svg.LineElement.description: The SVGLineElement interface provides access to the properties of line elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

js.html.svg.LinearGradientElement.name: LinearGradientElement
js.html.svg.LinearGradientElement.description: The SVGLinearGradientElement interface corresponds to the linearGradient element.

js.html.svg.MPathElement.name: MPathElement
js.html.svg.MPathElement.description: The SVGMPathElement interface corresponds to the mpath element.

js.html.svg.MaskElement.name: MaskElement
js.html.svg.MaskElement.description: The SVGMaskElement interface provides access to the properties of mask elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

js.html.svg.MetadataElement.name: MetadataElement
js.html.svg.MetadataElement.description: The SVGMetadataElement interface corresponds to the metadata element.

js.html.svg.Number.name: Number
js.html.svg.Number.description: The SVGNumber interface corresponds to the number basic data type.

js.html.svg.NumberList.name: NumberList
js.html.svg.NumberList.description: The SVGNumberList defines a list of SVGNumber objects.

js.html.svg.PathElement.name: PathElement
js.html.svg.PathElement.description: The SVGPathElement interface corresponds to the path element.

js.html.svg.PatternElement.name: PatternElement
js.html.svg.PatternElement.description: The SVGPatternElement interface corresponds to the pattern element.

js.html.svg.Point.name: Point
js.html.svg.Point.description: An SVGPoint represents a 2D or 3D point in the SVG coordinate system.

js.html.svg.PolygonElement.name: PolygonElement
js.html.svg.PolygonElement.description: The SVGPolygonElement interface provides access to the properties of polygon elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

js.html.svg.PolylineElement.name: PolylineElement
js.html.svg.PolylineElement.description: The SVGPolylineElement interface provides access to the properties of polyline elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

js.html.svg.PreserveAspectRatio.name: PreserveAspectRatio
js.html.svg.PreserveAspectRatio.description: The SVGPreserveAspectRatio interface corresponds to the preserveAspectRatio attribute, which is available for some of SVG's elements.

js.html.svg.RadialGradientElement.name: RadialGradientElement
js.html.svg.RadialGradientElement.description: The SVGRadialGradientElement interface corresponds to the RadialGradient element.

js.html.svg.Rect.name: Rect
js.html.svg.Rect.description: The SVGRect represents a rectangle. Rectangles consist of an x and y coordinate pair identifying a minimum x value, a minimum y value, and a width and height, which are constrained to be non-negative.

js.html.svg.RectElement.name: RectElement
js.html.svg.RectElement.description: The SVGRectElement interface provides access to the properties of rect elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

js.html.svg.SVGElement.name: SVGElement
js.html.svg.SVGElement.description: The SVGSVGElement interface provides access to the properties of svg elements, as well as methods to manipulate them. This interface contains also various miscellaneous commonly-used utility methods, such as matrix operations and the ability to control the time of redraw on visual rendering devices.

js.html.svg.ScriptElement.name: ScriptElement
js.html.svg.ScriptElement.description: The SVGScriptElement interface corresponds to the SVG script element.

js.html.svg.SetElement.name: SetElement
js.html.svg.SetElement.description: The SVGSetElement interface corresponds to the set element.

js.html.svg.StopElement.name: StopElement
js.html.svg.StopElement.description: The SVGStopElement interface corresponds to the stop element.

js.html.svg.StringList.name: StringList
js.html.svg.StringList.description: The SVGStringList defines a list of DOMString objects.

js.html.svg.StyleElement.name: StyleElement
js.html.svg.StyleElement.description: The SVGStyleElement interface corresponds to the SVG style element.

js.html.svg.SwitchElement.name: SwitchElement
js.html.svg.SwitchElement.description: The SVGSwitchElement interface corresponds to the switch element.

js.html.svg.SymbolElement.name: SymbolElement
js.html.svg.SymbolElement.description: The SVGSymbolElement interface corresponds to the symbol element.

js.html.svg.TSpanElement.name: TSpanElement
js.html.svg.TSpanElement.description: The SVGTSpanElement interface represents a tspan element.

js.html.svg.TextContentElement.name: TextContentElement
js.html.svg.TextContentElement.description: The SVGTextContentElement interface is implemented by elements that support rendering child text content. It is inherited by various text-related interfaces, such as SVGTextElement, SVGTSpanElement, SVGTRefElement, SVGAltGlyphElement and SVGTextPathElement.

js.html.svg.TextElement.name: TextElement
js.html.svg.TextElement.description: The SVGTextElement interface corresponds to the text elements.

js.html.svg.TextPathElement.name: TextPathElement
js.html.svg.TextPathElement.description: The SVGTextPathElement interface corresponds to the textPath element.

js.html.svg.TextPositioningElement.name: TextPositioningElement
js.html.svg.TextPositioningElement.description: The SVGTextPositioningElement interface is implemented by elements that support attributes that position individual text glyphs. It is inherited by SVGTextElement, SVGTSpanElement, SVGTRefElement and SVGAltGlyphElement.

js.html.svg.TitleElement.name: TitleElement
js.html.svg.TitleElement.description: The SVGTitleElement interface corresponds to the title element.

js.html.svg.Transform.name: Transform
js.html.svg.Transform.description: SVGTransform is the interface for one of the component transformations within an SVGTransformList; thus, an SVGTransform object corresponds to a single component (e.g., scale(…) or matrix(…)) within a transform attribute.

js.html.svg.TransformList.name: TransformList
js.html.svg.TransformList.description: The SVGTransformList defines a list of SVGTransform objects.

js.html.svg.UnitTypes.name: UnitTypes
js.html.svg.UnitTypes.description: The SVGUnitTypes interface defines a commonly used set of constants used for reflecting gradientUnits, patternContentUnits and other similar attributes.

js.html.svg.UseElement.name: UseElement
js.html.svg.UseElement.description: The SVGUseElement interface corresponds to the use element.

js.html.svg.ViewElement.name: ViewElement
js.html.svg.ViewElement.description: The SVGViewElement interface provides access to the properties of view elements, as well as methods to manipulate them.

js.html.svg.ZoomAndPan.name: ZoomAndPan
js.html.svg.ZoomAndPan.description: The SVGZoomAndPan interfaceis used to reflect the zoomAndPan attribute, and is mixed in to other interfaces for elements that support this attribute.

js.html.webgl.ActiveInfo.name: ActiveInfo
js.html.webgl.ActiveInfo.description: The WebGLActiveInfo interface is part of the WebGL API and represents the information returned by calling the WebGLRenderingContext.getActiveAttrib() and WebGLRenderingContext.getActiveUniform() methods.

js.html.webgl.Buffer.name: Buffer
js.html.webgl.Buffer.description: The WebGLBuffer interface is part of the WebGL API and represents an opaque buffer object storing data such as vertices or colors.

js.html.webgl.ContextEvent.name: ContextEvent
js.html.webgl.ContextEvent.description: The WebContextEvent interface is part of the WebGL API and is an interface for an event that is generated in response to a status change to the WebGL rendering context.

js.html.webgl.Framebuffer.name: Framebuffer
js.html.webgl.Framebuffer.description: The WebGLFramebuffer interface is part of the WebGL API and represents a collection of buffers that serve as a rendering destination.

js.html.webgl.Program.name: Program
js.html.webgl.Program.description: The WebGLProgram is part of the WebGL API and is a combination of two compiled WebGLShaders consisting of a vertex shader and a fragment shader (both written in GLSL). These are then linked into a usable program.

js.html.webgl.Query.name: Query
js.html.webgl.Query.description: The WebGLQuery interface is part of the WebGL 2 API and provides ways to asynchronously query for information. By default, occlusion queries and primitive queries are available.

js.html.webgl.Renderbuffer.name: Renderbuffer
js.html.webgl.Renderbuffer.description: The WebGLRenderbuffer interface is part of the WebGL API and represents a buffer that can contain an image, or can be source or target of an rendering operation.

js.html.webgl.RenderingContext.name: RenderingContext
js.html.webgl.RenderingContext.description: The WebGLRenderingContext interface provides the OpenGL ES 2.0 rendering context for the drawing surface of an HTML canvas element.

js.html.webgl.Sampler.name: Sampler
js.html.webgl.Sampler.description: The WebGLSampler interface is part of the WebGL 2 API and stores sampling parameters for WebGLTexture access inside of a shader.

js.html.webgl.Shader.name: Shader
js.html.webgl.Shader.description: The WebGLShader is part of the WebGL API and can either be a vertex or a fragment shader. A WebGLProgram requires both types of shaders.

js.html.webgl.ShaderPrecisionFormat.name: ShaderPrecisionFormat
js.html.webgl.ShaderPrecisionFormat.description: The WebGLShaderPrecisionFormat interface is part of the WebGL API and represents the information returned by calling the WebGLRenderingContext.getShaderPrecisionFormat() method.

js.html.webgl.Sync.name: Sync
js.html.webgl.Sync.description: The WebGLSync interface is part of the WebGL 2 API and is used to synchronize activities between the GPU and the application.

js.html.webgl.Texture.name: Texture
js.html.webgl.Texture.description: The WebGLTexture interface is part of the WebGL API and represents an opaque texture object providing storage and state for texturing operations.

js.html.webgl.TransformFeedback.name: TransformFeedback
js.html.webgl.TransformFeedback.description: The WebGLTransformFeedback interface is part of the WebGL 2 API and enables transform feedback, which is the process of capturing primitives generated by vertex processing. It allows to preserve the post-transform rendering state of an object and resubmit this data multiple times.

js.html.webgl.UniformLocation.name: UniformLocation
js.html.webgl.UniformLocation.description: The WebGLUniformLocation interface is part of the WebGL API and represents the location of a uniform variable in a shader program.

js.html.webgl.VertexArrayObject.name: VertexArrayObject
js.html.webgl.VertexArrayObject.description: The WebGLVertexArrayObject interface is part of the WebGL 2 API, represents vertex array objects (VAOs) pointing to vertex array data, and provides names for different sets of vertex data.

js.html.webgl.WebGL2RenderingContext.name: WebGL2RenderingContext
js.html.webgl.WebGL2RenderingContext.description: The WebGL2RenderingContext interface provides the OpenGL ES 3.0 rendering context for the drawing surface of an HTML canvas element.

js.html.webgl.GL.name: GL
js.html.webgl.GL.description: An alias for accessing GL constants more naturally.

js.html.webgl.GL2.name: GL2
js.html.webgl.GL2.description: An alias for accessing GL constants more naturally.

js.lib.intl.Collator.name: Collator
js.lib.intl.Collator.description:
The Collator object is a constructor for collators, objects that enable language
sensitive string comparison.

js.lib.intl.DateTimeFormat.name: DateTimeFormat
js.lib.intl.DateTimeFormat.description:
The DateTimeFormat object is a constructor for objects that enable language-sensitive
date and time formatting.

js.lib.intl.NumberFormat.name: NumberFormat
js.lib.intl.NumberFormat.description: The NumberFormat object is a constructor for objects that enable language sensitive number formatting.

js.lib.intl.PluralRules.name: PluralRules
js.lib.intl.PluralRules.description:
The PluralRules object is a constructor for objects that enable plural sensitive formatting
and plural language rules.

js.lib.intl.RelativeTimeFormat.name: RelativeTimeFormat
js.lib.intl.RelativeTimeFormat.description:
The RelativeTimeFormat object is a constructor for objects that enable language-sensitive
relative time formatting.

js.lib.webassembly.CompileError.name: CompileError
js.lib.webassembly.CompileError.description:
A WebAssembly CompileError object indicates an error during WebAssembly
decoding or validation.

js.lib.webassembly.Global.name: Global
js.lib.webassembly.Global.description:
A WebAssembly Global object represents a global variable instance, accessible from
both JavaScript and importable/exportable across one or more WebAssembly Module instances.
This allows dynamic linking of multiple modules.

js.lib.webassembly.Instance.name: Instance
js.lib.webassembly.Instance.description:
A WebAssembly Instance object is a stateful, executable instance of a WebAssembly Module.
Instance objects contain all the Exported WebAssembly functions
that allow calling into WebAssembly code from JavaScript.

js.lib.webassembly.LinkError.name: LinkError
js.lib.webassembly.LinkError.description:
A WebAssembly LinkError object indicates an error during module instantiation
(besides traps from the start function).

js.lib.webassembly.Memory.name: Memory
js.lib.webassembly.Memory.description:
A new WebAssembly Memory object which is a resizable ArrayBuffer that holds the raw bytes of memory
accessed by a WebAssembly WebAssembly Instance.

js.lib.webassembly.Module.name: Module
js.lib.webassembly.Module.description:
A WebAssembly Module object contains stateless WebAssembly code that has already
been compiled by the browser and can be efficiently shared with Workers,
and instantiated multiple times. To instantiate the module, call
the secondary overload of WebAssembly.instantiate().

js.lib.webassembly.RuntimeError.name: RuntimeError
js.lib.webassembly.RuntimeError.description:
A WebAssembly RuntimeError object is thrown whenever WebAssembly specifies a
trap.

js.lib.webassembly.Table.name: Table
js.lib.webassembly.Table.description: A Table object of the given size and element type.

lua.lib.luautf8.Utf8.name: Utf8
lua.lib.luautf8.Utf8.description:
These are all externs for the lua-utf8 library, which functions
as an additional set of string tools.

python.lib.net.Socket.name: Socket
python.lib.net.Socket.description: A TCP socket class : allow you to both connect to a given server and exchange messages or start your own server and wait for connections.

python.lib.socket.Socket.name: Socket
python.lib.socket.Socket.description: A TCP socket class : allow you to both connect to a given server and exchange messages or start your own server and wait for connections.

js.html.webgl.extension.ANGLEInstancedAr.name: ANGLEInstancedArrays
js.html.webgl.extension.ANGLEInstancedAr.description: The ANGLE_instanced_arrays extension is part of the WebGL API and allows to draw the same object, or groups of similar objects multiple times, if they share the same vertex data, primitive count and type.

js.html.webgl.extension.EXTBlendMinmax.name: EXTBlendMinmax
js.html.webgl.extension.EXTBlendMinmax.description: The EXT_blend_minmax extension is part of the WebGL API and extends blending capabilities by adding two new blend equations: the minimum or maximum color components of the source and destination colors.

js.html.webgl.extension.EXTColorBufferHa.name: EXTColorBufferHalfFloat
js.html.webgl.extension.EXTColorBufferHa.description: The EXT_color_buffer_half_float extension is part of the WebGL API and adds the ability to render to 16-bit floating-point color buffers.

js.html.webgl.extension.EXTDisjointTimer.name: EXTDisjointTimerQuery
js.html.webgl.extension.EXTDisjointTimer.description: The EXT_disjoint_timer_query extension is part of the WebGL API and provides a way to measure the duration of a set of GL commands, without stalling the rendering pipeline.

js.html.webgl.extension.EXTSrgb.name: EXTSrgb
js.html.webgl.extension.EXTSrgb.description: The EXT_sRGB extension is part of the WebGL API and adds sRGB support to textures and framebuffer objects.

js.html.webgl.extension.EXTTextureFilter.name: EXTTextureFilterAnisotropic
js.html.webgl.extension.EXTTextureFilter.description: The EXT_texture_filter_anisotropic extension is part of the WebGL API and exposes two constants for anisotropic filtering (AF).

js.html.webgl.extension.OESStandardDeriv.name: OESStandardDerivatives
js.html.webgl.extension.OESStandardDeriv.description: The OES_standard_derivatives extension is part of the WebGL API and adds the GLSL derivative functions dFdx, dFdy, and fwidth.

js.html.webgl.extension.OESTextureHalfFl.name: OESTextureHalfFloat
js.html.webgl.extension.OESTextureHalfFl.description: The OES_texture_half_float extension is part of the WebGL API and adds texture formats with 16- (aka half float) and 32-bit floating-point components.

js.html.webgl.extension.OESVertexArrayOb.name: OESVertexArrayObject
js.html.webgl.extension.OESVertexArrayOb.description: The OES_vertex_array_object extension is part of the WebGL API and provides vertex array objects (VAOs) which encapsulate vertex array states. These objects keep pointers to vertex data and provide names for different sets of vertex data.

js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLColorBuffer.name: WEBGLColorBufferFloat
js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLColorBuffer.description: The WEBGL_color_buffer_float extension is part of the WebGL API and adds the ability to render to 32-bit floating-point color buffers.

js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLCompressedT.name: WEBGLCompressedTextureAstc
js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLCompressedT.description: The WEBGL_compressed_texture_astc extension is part of the WebGL API and exposes Adaptive Scalable Texture Compression (ASTC) compressed texture formats to WebGL.

js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLCompressedT.name: WEBGLCompressedTextureAtc
js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLCompressedT.description: The WEBGL_compressed_texture_atc extension is part of the WebGL API and exposes 3 ATC compressed texture formats. ATC is a proprietary compression algorithm for compressing textures on handheld devices.

js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLCompressedT.name: WEBGLCompressedTextureEtc
js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLCompressedT.description: The WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc extension is part of the WebGL API and exposes 10 ETC/EAC compressed texture formats.

js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLCompressedT.name: WEBGLCompressedTextureEtc1
js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLCompressedT.description: The WEBGL_compressed_texture_etc1 extension is part of the WebGL API and exposes the ETC1 compressed texture format.

js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLCompressedT.name: WEBGLCompressedTexturePvrtc
js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLCompressedT.description: The WEBGL_compressed_texture_pvrtc extension is part of the WebGL API and exposes four PVRTC compressed texture formats.

js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLCompressedT.name: WEBGLCompressedTextureS3tc
js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLCompressedT.description: The WEBGL_compressed_texture_s3tc extension is part of the WebGL API and exposes four S3TC compressed texture formats.

js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLCompressedT.name: WEBGLCompressedTextureS3tcSrgb
js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLCompressedT.description: The WEBGL_compressed_texture_s3tc_srgb extension is part of the WebGL API and exposes four S3TC compressed texture formats for the sRGB colorspace.

js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLDebugRender.name: WEBGLDebugRendererInfo
js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLDebugRender.description: The WEBGL_debug_renderer_info extension is part of the WebGL API and exposes two constants with information about the graphics driver for debugging purposes.

js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLDepthTextur.name: WEBGLDepthTexture
js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLDepthTextur.description: The WEBGL_depth_texture extension is part of the WebGL API and defines 2D depth and depth-stencil textures.

js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLDrawBuffers.name: WEBGLDrawBuffers
js.html.webgl.extension.WEBGLDrawBuffers.description: The WEBGL_draw_buffers extension is part of the WebGL API and enables a fragment shader to write to several textures, which is useful for deferred shading, for example.

ArrayAccess.name: ArrayAccess
ArrayAccess.description:
ArrayAccess is used to indicate a class that can be accessed using brackets.
The type parameter represents the type of the elements stored.

Date.name: Date
Date.description:
The Date class provides a basic structure for date and time related
information. Date instances can be created by

DateTools.name: DateTools
DateTools.description:
The DateTools class contains some extra functionalities for handling Date
instances and timestamps.

EReg.name: EReg
EReg.description: The EReg class represents regular expressions.

IntIterator.name: IntIterator
IntIterator.description: IntIterator is used for implementing interval iterations.

Lambda.name: Lambda
Lambda.description:
The Lambda class is a collection of methods to support functional
programming. It is ideally used with using Lambda and then acts as an
extension to Iterable types.

Math.name: Math
Math.description: This class defines mathematical functions and constants.

Reflect.name: Reflect
Reflect.description:
The Reflect API is a way to manipulate values dynamically through an
abstract interface in an untyped manner. Use with care.

Std.name: Std
Std.description: The Std class provides standard methods for manipulating basic types.

StringBuf.name: StringBuf
StringBuf.description:
A String buffer is an efficient way to build a big string by appending small
elements together.

StringTools.name: StringTools
StringTools.description:
This class provides advanced methods on Strings. It is ideally used with
using StringTools and then acts as an extension

Sys.name: Sys
Sys.description:
This class provides access to various base functions of system platforms.
Look in the sys package for more system APIs.

Type.name: Type
Type.description: The Haxe Reflection API allows retrieval of type information at runtime.

Any.name: Any
Any.description: Any is a type that is compatible with any other in both ways.

Bool.name: Bool
Bool.description: The standard Boolean type, which can either be true or false.

Class.name: Class
Class.description: An abstract type that represents a Class.

Dynamic.name: Dynamic
Dynamic.description: Dynamic is a special type which is compatible with all other types.

Enum.name: Enum
Enum.description: An abstract type that represents an Enum type.

EnumValue.name: EnumValue
EnumValue.description:
An abstract type that represents any enum value.
See Type for the Haxe Reflection API.

Float.name: Float
Float.description: The standard Float type, this is a double-precision IEEE 64bit float.

Int.name: Int
Int.description: The standard Int type. Its precision depends on the platform.

Null.name: Null
Null.description:
Null<T> is a wrapper that can be used to make the basic types Int,
Float and Bool nullable on static targets.

UInt.name: UInt
UInt.description:
The unsigned Int type is only defined for Flash and C#.
Simulate it for other platforms.

UnicodeString.name: UnicodeString
UnicodeString.description: This abstract provides consistent cross-target unicode support.

Void.name: Void
Void.description: The standard Void type. Only null values can be of the type Void.

ValueType.name: ValueType
ValueType.description: The different possible runtime types of a value.

Iterable.name: Iterable
Iterable.description:
An Iterable is a data structure which has an iterator() method.
See Lambda for generic functions on iterable structures.

Iterator.name: Iterator
Iterator.description: An Iterator is a structure that permits iteration over elements of type T.

KeyValueIterable.name: KeyValueIterable
KeyValueIterable.description:
A KeyValueIterable is a data structure which has a keyValueIterator()
method to iterate over key-value-pairs.

KeyValueIterator.name: KeyValueIterator
KeyValueIterator.description: A KeyValueIterator is an Iterator that has a key and a value.
